<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Jordan in Tourism Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 32 million U.S. dollar loan to Jordan for the second
tourism development project.
</P>
<P>
The project will help the country protect some of its most
important historical and ecological sites, including the
well-known Petra, while generating increased tourism income for
the country.
</P>
<P>
Urban rehabilitation, coupled with enforcement of land-use
plans, are mapped out under the project and are expected to lead
the improvements in the quality of life for the local
populations of Petra region, Jerash, Wadi Rum and Karak.
</P>
<P>
More than 1.1 million tourists visit Jordan every year.
Tourism is the country's second-largest generator of foreign
exchange after remittances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
