<HEADLINE> Indonesian FM to Visit Cambodia Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas will leave here Saturday morning for Phnom Penh to meet
with Cambodian Second Prime Minister Hun Sen, an official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
A Foreign Ministry official disclosed that Alatas' main mission
is to exchange views with Hun Sen on political crisis in that
country, but he did not elaborate on the topics they will discuss.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab
Chaiyasarn and Philippine Foreign Secretary Domingo Siazon will
also go to Phnom Penh tomorrow to meet with Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
As representatives of ASEAN, the three foreign ministers had
met with Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk, First Prime Minister
Norodom Ranariddh and Hun Sen separately last month in a bid to
help end the conflict in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) now groups
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand,
Vietnam, Laos and Myanmar. Cambodia was delayed to enter the
grouping because of political crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said earlier that ASEAN will never interfere in
Cambodia's internal affairs. He said if one of the two warring
factions opposed the ASEAN efforts, ASEAN will stop its mediation.
</P>
<P>
Alatas also said an agreement between the two warring factions,
namely, Cambodian People's Party led by Hun Sen and the FUNCINPEC
led by Norodom Ranariddh, plays a significant role in ending the
crisis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
