<HEADLINE> Bomb on Prison Vehicle Wound 4 in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- A remote-control car bomb
exploded in central Anatolia today, wounding four people in a
prison vehicle heading for court, a Turkish official said.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency quoted Kirsehir Deputy
Governor Osman Gurbuz as saying that the bomb was detonated when
the armored prison vehicle passed a car parked on a road near the
town of Akpinar.
</P>
<P>
Gurbuz said two soldiers, a driver and a prisoner were wounded
in the explosion, as the soldiers were accompanying eight accused
Islamic militants to a hearing in the capital of Ankara, some 180
kilometers away.
</P>
<P>
The defendants were accused of causing a hotel fire in 1993
which killed 37 intellectuals in Sivas, central Turkey.
</P>
<P>
No one claimed responsibility for the attack. The defendants
have been taken back to a Kirsehir prison by another vehicle.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a large-scale operation was launched by the
government in a bid to capture troublemakers in the
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
