<HEADLINE> 31 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces today
killed 31 rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in
military operations in eastern and southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that during the armed clashes two village guards were
also killed.
</P>
<P>
Three PKK members surrendered to the security forces in the
region, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency today quoted
Iraq's Kurdistan Democratic Party (KDP) officials, who declined
to be named, as saying that the KDP forces killed more than 200
PKK rebels in the last three months in northern Iraq, where the
rebels are sheltered.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war for
autonomy, which has claimed over 27,000 lives in eastern and
southeastern Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
