<HEADLINE> Swaziland to Produce Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland's first car
manufacturing firm has begun operation with an initial producing
capacity of 50 vehicles per month.
</P>
<P>
A South African company, Afinta Motor Corporation, will invest
25.5 million U.S Dollars in the next five years to help the firm,
according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland Transport Minister Dumsani Masango said in Mbabane
today that the firm will help improve the kingdom's transport
industry and give employment to 1,000 local citizens.
</P>
<P>
At its full capacity, the motor company will be putting out
250 units to be sold in Swaziland and other African countries.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the car manufacturer said it already has orders
at home, Malawi, Mozambique and eastern Africa. 
