<HEADLINE> Moya, Dosedel to Clash in Amsterdam Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Carlos Moya of Spain
overwhelmed fourth-seeded Magnus Norman of Sweden to advance to
the final of the 500,000 U.S. dollars ATP Tour clay court tennis
tournament in Amsterdam, Netherlands on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Moya, ranked 10th in the world and a finalist at the Australian
Open in January, defeated 29th-ranked Norman 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Moya will play unseeded Czech player Slava Dosedel in the final
after Dosedel edged Marcelo Filipini of Uruguay 7-6 (7-5), 6-2.
</P>
</TEXT>
