<HEADLINE> Symposium Held On Chinese Revolutionary History Films </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Noteworthy achievements have been
made over the past ten years in the production of films and TV
dramas reflecting the history of the Chinese Revolution, and such
shows are important to China, a high-ranking party official said
today.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, a member of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Committee Politburo, offered the praise at the closing of
a three-day national symposium on the making of movies and TV
programs about the Revolution.
</P>
<P>
Ding, also head of the Propaganda Department of the CPC Central
Committee, said these films and TV dramas help to educate people,
especially the young, about patriotism and the history of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
In the ten years since a group was set up to oversee the
shooting of major films and TV programs featuring the history of
the Revolution, 25 movies and 89 TV dramas on the subject have
been made. 
</P>
</TEXT>
