<HEADLINE> Anti-Taliban Jet Fighter Raids Taliban's Positions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A jet fighter belonging to
forces opposing the Afghan Islamic Taliban militia today pounded
the militia's positions north of Kabul in an attempt to break a
week-long deadlock.
</P>
<P>
However, the frontlines were still located about 20 km north of
Kabul, where Taliban and their rivals have been fighting for the
last week, according to the reports monitored here today.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have failed to gain any significant ground north of
the beleaguered Afghan capital though they kept battling each
other's positions with heavy artillery and machine gun fire.
</P>
<P>
Slightly more than two weeks ago, the forces loyal to the
Afghan former military chief Ahmad Masood began a major offensive
which has brought them to within rocket range of Kabul.  
</P>
</TEXT>
