<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Envoy Accused of Creating Chaos in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Somali faction led by
Osman Hassan Ali Atto today accused the Italian special envoy to
Somalia Giuseppe Cassini of creating chaos, instability and
releasing false information about the country's situation.
</P>
<P>
In a three-page press statement issued today at the
headquarters of Osman Ali Atto in south Mogadishu, Cassini was
also accused of posing obstacles to the reconciliation efforts
undertaken by the National Salvation Council (NSC), the peace
efforts by the regional Inter-Governmental Authority on
Development (IGAD) and the implementation of the peace agreements
reached by Somali factions in Nairobi, Sana and Cairo.
</P>
<P>
The United Somali Congress of Somali National Alliance
(USC/SNA) led by Osman Atto has called on the Italian government
to clear its political attitude towards Somalia and play a
neutral role in Somalia's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Italian envoy as a person who has fallen far
behind being entrusted to lead the relationship between Somalia
and Italy, USC/SNA also accused Giuseppe Cassini for being
responsible for the failure of the recent Italian diplomacy in
Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Cassini has been lobbying for the creation of a local
authority for Benadir region in Mogadishu during his six-month
mission.
</P>
<P>
His political failure surfaced following the visit of Rino
Serri, Italian Under Secretary of State, in the capital four days
ago when the latter failed to bring all of the Somali factions
together. 
</P>
</TEXT>
