<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangsu to Spend 10 Billion Yuan on Flood Control Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
plans to spend 9.8 billion yuan (1.19 billion US dollars) on flood
control projects in the Huaihe River and Taihu Lake basins by the
year 2005.
</P>
<P>
The central government is also to give 2.88 billion yuan ( 340
million dollars) for the work by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Huaihe River and Taihu Lake basins account for most of the
area of east China's Jiangsu Province and often suffer from
flooding and excessive rainfall.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, the province has channeled 2.48 billion yuan (300
million dollars) into anti-flood projects in the two basins.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu also will set up a special fund for water conservation
projects in the two areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
