<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT August 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat
Saturday accused Israel of having virtually declared a war upon
the Palestinians by toughening security measures on them.
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodian Second Prime Minister Hun Sen Saturday
held talks with a visiting ASEAN delegation and expressed
satisfaction over the results of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The three-man ASEAN delegation of foreign ministers from
Indonesia, Thailand and the Philippines, is now on its second trip
here within two weeks in an effort to seek solution to the current
political situation of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
ALGIERS -- Up to 80 villagers were slain by a terrorist group
last Thursday in the Algerian region of Blida, 50 kilometers south
the capital Algiers, according to informed sources Saturday.
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair named 57 new peers
Saturday, the largest number of peers appointed in a single
announcement in modern times.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran and Syria issued here Friday night a joint
statement, calling for an end to the Israeli occupation of all
Arab lands, Iran's official news agency IRNA reported Saturday.
</P>
