<HEADLINE> Typhoon Victor Hits Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Typhoon Victor made a direct
hit on Hong Kong at 8 p.m. today, local observatory reported.
</P>
<P>
The first typhoon of the season was centered over Hong Kong by
8 o'clock this evening and was moving north at a speed of about 22
km an hour towards the Pearl River Delta.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Observatory said that winds would decrease as
Typhoon Victor moved northwards.
</P>
<P>
Last time a same hurricane-force wind attacked Hong Kong in
1983, killing ten people and injuring 300.
</P>
<P>
Typhoon Victor has brought Hong Kong to a standstill. Almost
all transport services, ranging from buses to trams, ferries and
Kowloon-Canton Railway, suspended this afternoon as the typhoon
was edging closer to Hong Kong at a speed of 18 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
More than 180 flights have been delayed or canceled due to the
stormy weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
