<HEADLINE> Guangxi Receives More Overseas Tourists in January-June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region hosted more than 250,000 overseas tourists in
the first half of this year, up nearly 20 percent from the same
1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Tourism earned the region 74.5 million US dollars in foreign
exchange, a rise of 19 percent, according to statistics from local
tourism bureau.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi is rich in tourism resources, particularly the local
mountains, rivers, ethnic folklore, and cultural relics.
</P>
<P>
The province expects one million overseas tourists by the year
2000, with tourism earnings reaching 400 million to 500 million US
dollars in foreign currency, according to local tourism sources.
</P>
</TEXT>
