<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Guo Dandan Wins World Cup Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Girl Guo Dandan defeated
other rivals to win the second round of the World Cup freestyle
skiing tournament in Mt Buller, Australia on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese collected 179.80 for the top place followed by
Canada's Veronica Brenner in 169.80 and Australia's Kirstie
Marshall in 165.83.
</P>
<P>
19-year-old Guo produced a full-double-full routine, a triple
somersault with four twists, to earn high points because of the
high degree of difficulty.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Chen Hongbin said Chinese skiers were training
with the nation's best divers and "We're learning a lot from the
divers."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese only appeared on the World Cup scene last year but
Marshall said, technically, they were performing their jumps
"beautifully".
</P>
<P>
Eric Bergoust of the United States earned 242.53 to take the
men's event. The second place went to American Britt Swartley
with 237.34 and Jeff Bean of Canada came third with 227.80.
</P>
<P>
Canada's world champion Nicolas Fontaine, winner of Friday's
season-opening event at the same venue, was relegated to sixth.
</P>
</TEXT>
