<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 660,000 Jobless Tianjin Residents Re-employed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The city government of Tianjin
has helped 660,000 local unemployed people find work in the past
three years, according to sources with the Poverty-Relief and
Re-employment Office in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Hua Shaozeng, head of the Labor Bureau in Tianjin, said that by
the end of the first six months of this year, the re-employment
rate in this north China city stood at 80 percent -- a proud
showing over the 50 percent required by the central government.
</P>
<P>
Bureau figures also show that there are still more than 50,000
unemployed people in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Governor Li Shenglin told Xinhua that the city has created
over 20 job channels through the restructuring of industries and
the development of urban-rural joint ventures and the service
industry.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of the tourism, electronic telecommunication,
real estate and insurance sectors also has helped to produce job
opportunities, he said.
</P>
<P>
The insurance sector alone has recruited over 1,000 jobless to
become life insurance salesmen this year.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, starting in 1990, self-employed businessmen,
private companies and foreign-funded enterprises in the city have
provided 450,000 jobs, mostly for the unemployed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
