<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Port Handles More Containers in January-June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai port in east China
handled 1.12 million TEUs of containers in the first half of this
year, up 31 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Port authorities estimated that the port will handle 2.3
million TEUs of containers this year.
</P>
<P>
In the January-June period, imports received at the port
amounted to 14.2 million tons, up 7.5 percent, while exports rose
22.8 percent to 8.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Xu Delin, an official of the port, attributed the increase to
the sound overall economic operation in China, the advantageous
location of the port, the upgrading of management, and the
expansion of sea, highway, and railway transport routes.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Shanghai port handled nearly two million TEUs of
containers, ranking 17th among the world's large ports.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
