<HEADLINE> Fujian To Build New Railway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province plans
to build a 17.5 km railway line from the special economic zone of
Xiamen to Haichang port.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Railways and the city of Xiamen will jointly
invest 181 million yuan into the project, which will cover 87 ha
of land.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities believe the new line will further improve the
investment environment of the Haichang port area.
</P>
<P>
In 1989 the State Council approved the building of a special
investment area for Taiwan business people in Haichang. So far, 85
overseas-funded enterprises have been set up at the port area,
involving a total investment of 1.18 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Haichang is expected to have a combined industrial output of
4.5 billion yuan in 1997. 
</P>
