<HEADLINE> Water Supply Project in Fujian Going Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Work is going smoothly on a water
supply project in east China's Fujian Province, which plans to
divert water from the Jinjiang River to the Xiaocuo Development
Zone in the city of Quanzhou.
</P>
<P>
The new water supply line will be 61.7 km.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, 16.3 km of tunnels had been dug. It is
estimated that the project will be finished by year-end.
</P>
<P>
The project started in 1993, with a total investment of 310
million yuan. The designed water flow will reach three cubic
meters per second, and the annual water supply capacity, 90
million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
