<HEADLINE> 2 Drug Traffickers Arrested in Karachi Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's drug enforcement
forces today arrested two drug traffickers at the Karachi
International Airport following recovery of 1,350 grams of heroin
powder from their possession.
</P>
<P>
Shahid Mahmood, a Pakistani national and Zahid Hussain having
Spanish nationality, were intercepted by the drug enforcement
staff at the airport on ground of suspicion, according to a report
by Associated Press of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
Both of them claimed to be brothers when they reported at the
departure counter to take a Frankfurt-bound flight of Pakistan
International Airlines (PIA), the report said.
</P>
<P>
A last minute examination of their baggage and belongings led
to the recovery of 1,350 grams off-white heroin powder which was
concealed under the insteps of shoes worn by them, the report
said.  
</P>
