<HEADLINE> Real Estate Market in Shanghai Thriving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's real estate market
has continued to prosper since the beginning of this year,
information from Shanghai Real Estate Trading Center shows.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, registered sales of the combined
floor space of open-market apartments for the first half of this
year went up by 92 percent in a year-on-year comparison.
</P>
<P>
And more Shanghainese are opting buy rather than rent an
apartment.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the center also reveal that the municipality
has reported a spiraling increase in the total floor space of
apartments sold in advance of occupancy. A 20 percent increase in
land transfers was also recorded.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute a number of factors to the city's thriving
real estate market, including the reduction of real estate
development costs, increased marketing efforts by real estate
developers, housing loans offered by different banks to
individuals and change in people's attitude toward buying
purchasing housing.
</P>
<P>
A survey has shown that at least 60 percent individual homeowners
are middle-aged and young people.
</P>
</TEXT>
