<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 80 Massacred in Blida, Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Up to 80 villagers were slain by a
terrorist group last Thursday in the Algerian region of Blida, 50
kilometers south the capital Algiers, according to informed
sources today.
</P>
<P>
The incident is the most horrible massacre in terms of the
number of victims since the parliamentary elections on June 5.
</P>
<P>
Many of the victims belong to one family including the old and
children with their throats slit.
</P>
<P>
It came in retaliation for the twelve-day combing operation
launched by the Algerian security forces two weeks ago in Tebessa
province, 70 kilometers west of Algiers.
</P>
<P>
During the combing operation, the security forces killed 130
terrorists at least and dozens of the terrorists surrendered.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 Algerian citizens have become victims of the
terrorist attacks over the last five days, bringing the figure to
more than 500 of the killed since early June.
</P>
<P>
Islamic militants have been waging an war against the
government since 1992 when the government canceled elections that
the Islamic Salvation Front was believed to win. More than 60,000
people have been killed in the five years of insurgency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
