<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host African Workshop on Community </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will host in November an
All Africa Workshop seeking ways to use community service as an
alternative to imprisonment, Justice Paddington Garwe said on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Garwe said, community service was being widely viewed as a
model for the third world, which was why Zimbabwe, through its
experience, had been chosen to host the conference.
</P>
<P>
The conference would be sponsored by the European Commission.
</P>
<P>
Garwe was speaking at a ceremony to officially hand over the
community service scheme to the Zimbabwean government from a
non-governmental organisation.
</P>
<P>
''The hosting of this conference will help put Zimbabwe on the
international map,'' said Garwe, adding, ''It is gratifying to
note that both the European Commission and the British High
Commission will continue to assist the scheme.''
</P>
<P>
A Zimbabwean justice, Yunus Omerjee, who is also Permanent
Secretary for Legal and Parliamentary affairs, said preparations
for the conference had reached advanced stages.
</P>
<P>
The ministry was recruiting additional staff members for the
community service scheme, Omerjee added. 
</P>
