<HEADLINE> PNA Official: Israel Declares War on Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Council Speaker Ahmed
Queria said today that the measures taken by Israel against the
Palestinians in the wake of the Jerusalem bombings on Wednesday
are tantamount to a declaration of war.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Cairo-based Voice of Arabs radio, the
Palestinian official condemned the Israeli measures as "the
toughest ever to be taken against the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
After Wednesday's bombings which killed 15 people and injured
170 others, Israel suspended peace talks with the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA), imposed a total closure on the West Bank
and Gaza Strip and threatened to reenter Palestinian-ruled areas
to arrest militants.
</P>
<P>
"Declaring a war against the Palestinians would never
guarantee Israel's security," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government is the only one to be blamed for what
has happened, the Palestinian official said, adding that the
Israeli policies that include suspension of the peace march and
building of settlements have led to a state of frustration and
cast doubts on the outcome of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Queria called upon PNA President Yasser Arafat and Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to meet to "put matters to order
and decide whether to continue the peace march or not."
</P>
<P>
He said that the Israeli measures aim at "isolating the
Palestinians and starving them," warning that the Palestinians are
in a state of turmoil and they would never accept anything that
might harm their dignity.
</P>
<P>
"The peace march is really in a fix and its destiny is
seriously threatened," he cautioned.
</P>
<P>
The anti-peace process militants launched the strikes just
days after the Palestinian and Israeli negotiators agreed to
resume talks that have been frozen for four months over Israel's
decision to build a new Jewish neighborhood in East Jerusalem.
</P>
</TEXT>
