<HEADLINE> Nine Nepalese Die of Snake Bite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Nine people have died of snake
bite in Kanchanpur district of far-western Nepal since April, the
official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
They were among the 155 people brought for treatment in local
hospitals in the past four months, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
People bitten by snakes tend to go for traditional methods of
treatment, leading to the rising number of deaths, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, bites by cobras, which are common in this district,
are difficult to treat because this reptile tends to go for the
abdomen, chest, throat or forehead of its victims, the agency
quoted a doctor as saying.
</P>
<P>
The fact that snakes started crawling into houses since the
monsoon set in contributes to the rising cases of snake bites, the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
Deaths of snake bites in other parts of the country were also
reported.  
</P>
</TEXT>
