<HEADLINE> First Girl's Youth World Volleyball Championships Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, North Thailand, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The First
Girl's Youth World Volleyball Championship began here today at the
Chiang Mai Sports Complex.
</P>
<P>
In the inaugural match of the championship that took place this
morning, host Thailand defeated Nigeria 15-0, 15-2, 15-2.
</P>
<P>
A total of 16 teams of girls under-17 from around the world are
taking part in the preliminary stage on a round robin basis.
</P>
<P>
Representing the East Asia Region in the Championship are
Japan, South Korewa and Host Thailand.
</P>
<P>
China lost the chance because in the qualifying round held in
April this year in Yala, South Thailand, It placed third after
Japan and South Korea. Thailand, as host, is automatically
qualified in the world event, even though it won fourth place in
yala.
</P>
<P>
At the preliminary round, the 16 teams are divided into four
groups. Pool A has Nigeria, Italy, Czech Republic and Thailand;
pool B has Ukraine, Japan, Poland and Cuba; Pool C has Slovakia,
Dominica, Brazil and Netherlands; Pool D has South Korea, Russia,
Mauritius and Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Quarter-final competition will be held on august 8 and the
final match will take place on August 10. 
</P>
