<HEADLINE> Biryukova Injured in Women's Triple Jump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Anna Biryukova of Russia, the 1993
world champion and the first woman over 15 meters in the women's
triple jump, was taken to a hospital this morning when she
injuried her leg in the qualifying round at the 6th World
Athletics Championships here Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Russian underwent X-ray tests at the Athens Olympic Stadium
at first, where she was diagnosed with a rupture of the patelar
tendon.
