<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anti-Drug Campaign Should Focus on Masterminds: Ramos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
said today that the country's anti-drug campaign should focus on
druglords, financiers and other masterminds in drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
"Let us now make sure that the focus is on the higher-ups,
meaning, the heads, the lords, the masterminds and the financiers
of the drug trafficking in the Philippines," he said.
</P>
<P>
To win the war against drug dealers and lords, Ramos said, he
would meet separately with key officials of law enforcement
involved in the anti-drug campaign, including the Department of
National Defense, the Armed Forces of the Philippines, the
Department of Justice and the National Bureau of Investigation.
</P>
<P>
The president met with Interior and Local Governments Secretary
Robert Barbers, Philippine National Police Director General
Recaredo Sarmiento and other top officials Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said during the meeting that he was determined to employ
all the three services of the armed forces in the all-out war
against drug syndicates.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he ordered Justice Secretary Teofisto Guingona,
Defense Secretary Renato de Villa and Barbers to map out plans and
strategies to intensify the government's anti-drug campaign.
</P>
<P>
Fighting drugs was not only the job of the law enforcement
departments, Ramos said, adding the battle could only be won with
the active support and participation of the community.
</P>
<P>
He also told the police leadership to utilize the country's
links with international law enforcement agencies including the
Interpol, a body of more than 120 countries that keep track of
transnational crimes with focus on drug trafficking and terrorism.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
