<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Typhoon Victor Affects HK Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Most of the air, land and sea
transport services in Hong Kong were suspended today as Typhoon
Victor edges closer to the Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Official reports said that at 3 p.m., Victor was about 140
kilometers south of Hong Kong and moving north at 18 km an hour
towards the Pearl River Estuary.
</P>
<P>
On its present course Victor is expected to pass very close to
Hong Kong later today. At noon the Hong Kong Observatory announced
 the hoisting of tropical cyclone warning signal no. 8.
</P>
<P>
At Hong Kong's Kai Tak International Airport, 37 flight
arrivals have been diverted or delayed while six scheduled
arrivals have been canceled. On the departure side, 30 flights
have been delayed and 11 others canceled.
</P>
<P>
Many public traffic services, including the Peak Tram, Tramway
services, Lantau Link, some bus lines and harbor ferries, were
canceled. Motorists have been urged to keep off the roads.
</P>
<P>
Rains began to lash Hong Kong yesterday and are continuing
today. There have been nine reports of collapsed trees in Hong
Kong and Kowloon but no reports of injuries.
</P>
<P>
The SAR's Home Affairs Department has opened 35 temporary
shelters in various districts for people in need of refuge during
the bad weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
