<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Expects First Aircraft Carrier in Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's first aircraft carrier
built in Spain will arrive next Monday in Pattaya, a seaport on
Thailand's eastern coast, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The carrier, HTMS Chakrinaruebet, will be based in the Gulf of
Thailand and will serve as a flagship and assist in search and
rescue and disaster relief, Thai Navy Chief of Staff Adm. Thira
Hawochroen said.
</P>
<P>
The naval vessel with a full-load displacement of 11,485 tons
was built at Bazan's el Ferrol Yard in Spain. It reportedly can
carry 600 crew members and is equipped with six multi-mission
Sikorsky S-70b Seahawk helicopters and nine Matador AV-SS Harriers
formerly owned by Spain.  
</P>
</TEXT>
