<HEADLINE> HK Property Transactions surge 29 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The total number of Hong Kong's
property sale and purchase transactions rose by 29 percent last
month compared with June to reach 22,574, according to today's
Hong Kong Standard.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, total considerations jumped 38 percent to 112.3
billion HK dollars (14.40 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
An analyst said the sharp increase in the July transactions did
not conflict with the significant slowdown in the mass residential
market caused by the government's announcement that the supply of
land for housing and production of flats would be increased
substantially.
</P>
<P>
The number of property transactions in July was the second
largest so far this year after the record high of 25,572 recorded
in April. 
</P>
</TEXT>
