<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Airlines Plane Makes Emergency Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- An Indian Airlines (IA) flight
escaped unhurt when the plane made an emergency landing at the
Chennai Airport about 2,157 km southeast of New Delhi soon after
taking-off today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that all the 81 passengers and crew
members aboard the flight were safe.
</P>
<P>
A tire burst has forced the emergency landing, Airports
Authority of India (AAI) sources said.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the take-off, a ground flight safety staff member
noticed pieces of the tire strewn on the runway and immediately
alerted the air traffic control, which in turn alerted the pilot
of the flight and the pilot made an emergency landing.
</P>
<P>
The Chennai Airport was closed for about an hour to enable the
aircraft to make the safe landing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
