<HEADLINE> World Islamic Leaders Meet in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A Conference of the World Islamic
People's Leadership and the World Islamic Call Society was opened
here today.
</P>
<P>
About 125 foreign delegates, mainly leaders, intellectuals,
executive officials and dignitaries from different parts of the
Islamic and Arab world attended today's opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The conference will review developments in the third world with
reference to the situation of Muslims the world over, according to
the conference sources.
</P>
<P>
It will provide representatives of Islamic people's
organizations an opportunity to focus on problems confronting them
and strategies for their solutions.
</P>
<P>
The conference will also review hardships and obstacles placed
in the development and progress of third world Muslim countries
and their economies and study ways and means to overcome them, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony, M.H.M. Ashraff, Sri Lanka's Minister
of Port Development, Rehabilitation and Reconstruction, said when
the world today at the threshold of the 21st century is deeply
troubled without a satisfactory answer to the basic issues such as
poverty and human dignity, international meetings of this nature
provide additional opportunities to collectively reflect on
possible new strategies to meet new challenges.  
</P>
</TEXT>
