<HEADLINE> Malaria Deaths Decrease in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaria deaths in Zimbabwe
decreased by 50 percent in July in comparison with 1996, Health
and Child Welfare Minister Timothy Stamps said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting marking the end of the malaria season
Friday, Stamps attributed the downward trend to the government's
cooperation with Zeneca, a British company which supplied the
Zimbabwean ministry with 3,500 kg of icon, an insecticide used in
the control of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the ministry show that malaria deaths has
fallen from 3,000 in 1996 to 1,500 by the end of the malaria
season in July this year.
</P>
<P>
Also on Friday, Zeneca donated equipment such as protective
clothing and mosquito nets which worth one million Zimbabwe
Dollars (91,000 U.S Dollars) for use against malaria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
