<HEADLINE> Illegal Migrant Killed by Lions in S.Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A 18-year-old Mozambican
attempting to enter South Africa illegally was killed by lions in
the Kruger National Park.
</P>
<P>
The remains of Adam Chauke, were found on Friday near a road
in the game park in the northern part of South Africa, local
daily the Citizen reported today.
</P>
<P>
The park authorities believe that Chauke was killed by lions
on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
He was one of 11 people who crossed into South Africa by
jumping the park's boundary fence from Mozambique, police
spokesman in the park Ronel Otto said.
</P>
<P>
"Shortly after entering the park, the group encountered a herd
of buffalo, and some lions which were on the hunt. The group
evidently fled in various directions," Otto said.
</P>
<P>
The other 10 illegals were picked up by a defense force patrol
and were being held at a police station. They will be repatriated
to Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Four Mozambicans were killed by lions in the Kruger National
Park last week.
</P>
<P>
Over three million illegal immigrants from neighbouring
countries are currently staying in South Africa. 
</P>
