<HEADLINE> Grenade Attack Hits Ugandan Police Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A grenade was hurled last night
at a police post in Kampala, killing a girl and injuring at least
six people including three policemen.
</P>
<P>
It is the third grenade attack in the city in three days, the
local daily the New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Eye witnesses and police were quoted as saying that the
attackers who were riding a motor bike hurled the grenade at the
Nakulabye police post at 8.00 p.m. last night.
</P>
<P>
This brings to 10 the number of people killed and 72 the
people who were injured in grenade explosions in the past three
days in the city. The first two blasts occurred at Kibuye and
Natete on Wednesday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Police Inspector General Cosy Odomel said that hard-core armed
criminals and their colleagues who are still in prisons, are
retaliating against the police crack-down on them.
</P>
<P>
He said that all policemen had been told to be vigilant.
</P>
</TEXT>
