<HEADLINE> Breast-feeding Week Celebrated in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Babies are holding the spotlight
in Myanmar again as the country is celebrating the annual
Breast-Feeding week with various activities aimed at promoting its
Baby Friendly Project.
</P>
<P>
As part of celebrations of the event, nine "Baby-Friendly
townships" and 55 "Baby-Friendly hospitals" were named by the
Health Ministry at a ceremony on Friday on the first day of the
Week, which runs through next Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been celebrating the event since 1992. So far, 12
townships and 180 hospitals have been designated as baby-friendly.
</P>
<P>
The week features activities including poster and cartoon
competitions, debates and discussions with the main theme of
"Breast-feeding: Nature's Way", and workshops on Baby Friendly
Home Delivery Assessment.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official statistics, infant and
maternal mortality rates in Myanmar in 1996 were 47 and 0.9 per
1,000 births respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
