<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 2 (Xinhua) -- All three crew members were killed
in a helicopter crash in Russia on Friday, the Inter-fax news
agency reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred near the countryside in Uljanovsk
Prefecture, southeast of Moscow, at 6:20 p.m. local time when the
aircraft was on a training flight, sources of the Ministry of
Civil Defense and Emergency Situations were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
