<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African NGOs to Meet on Fund Raising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania will host the
fifth international fund-raising workshop next month to enhance
the capacity of Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs) and
Community Based Organizations (CBOs) to generate their funding.
</P>
<P>
Margareth Kasembe, the Chairperson of the NGOs National
Planning Committee of Tanzania, told reporters here Friday that
250 people from nine east and central African countries were
expected to attend the workshop in Arusha, northern Tanzania,
between September 7 and 10.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will introduce participants to alternatives and
non-traditional forms of fund raising, try to promote networking
among fund raisers in the region and to empower the participants
with knowledge and skills in fund raising.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Population Fund, Oxfam, International Fund
Raising Group, Norwegian Agency for Development have funded for
the workshop.
</P>
<P>
The fund raising workshop is part of a world-wide program of
NGOs. Workshops in the region since 1993, were held in Kenya in
1993 and in 1994, Ethiopia in 1995 and Uganda in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
