<HEADLINE> 5 Killed, 52 Injured in Wedding Ceremony in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Some unidentified gunmen killed
five and wounded 52 others attending a wedding ceremony in
southeastern Turkey late Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Anatolia News Agency reported this morning that the
armed group first threw bombs into the house where the wedding
ceremony was being held in Cizre town of Sirnak province at 22:00
local time (19:00 GMT) and then they opened fire at about 500 people
attending the ceremony with automatic rifles.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to the hospitals in the region for
treatment, said the agency, but no reason was given for the armed
attack.
</P>
<P>
The southeastern part of Turkey is an area where guerrillas of
the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party have been operating in a fight
to set up an independent Kurdish state.
</P>
<P>
It added that the investigations into the incident are
underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
