<HEADLINE> Fiat, Peugeot Likely to Forge Alliance in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Italian automobile major Fiat
and its French rival Peugeot are likely to strike a strategic
alliance in India, it is learnt here today.
</P>
<P>
Under the probable alliance, Peugeot may share its existing
manufacturing facility in the country with Fiat for the latter's
world car "Palio" project in India.
</P>
<P>
Fiat and Peugeot, which share manufacturing facilities through
similar alliances in other parts of the world, might repeat the
experiment in India as well once Fiat's acquisition of a majority
stake in India's Doshi-controlled Premier Automobiles Ltd. (PAL)
is finalized.
</P>
<P>
With its controlling stake in PAL, Fiat will hold a significant
stake in PAL-Peugeot and thus become a joint venture partner of
the French automobile giant even when the two compete in the
marketplace with their respective models, reliable sources said.
</P>
</TEXT>
