<HEADLINE> Albania to Promote Relations With China, Say President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani
said today his new government will further develop relations with
China and carry out effective cooperation with it.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani said in an interview with Xinhua that China has
achieved rapid economic growth in the past decades, setting an
example for economic development.
</P>
<P>
He highly praised China's economic reform and the road it
adheres to, which had been initiated by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed Hong Kong's return to China would
eventually lead to China's national reunification.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani said his government would follow a practical policy and
develop relations with big and small countries, especially its
neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian people desire cooperation with China in the
economic and other fields, he said, and the government should work
to improve the bilateral ties so as to benefit the two countries
and their people.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani said his government would make efforts to restore law
and order in the country and invigorate economy. Security is most
needed without which economic recovery will be affected,
especially foreign investment and economic assistance.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani, 53, former general secretary of the Socialist Party,
was elected president on July 24 to replace Sali Berisha. He is
the third president since the country's first multi-party
elections in 1991.
</P>
<P>
After he became president, Mejdani resigned from his post in
the Socialist Party and withdrew from the party as "a sign of
national unity." 
</P>
