<HEADLINE> Romania, Colombia Sign New Trade Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Romania and Colombia signed a
trade agreement today, replacing the one signed 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Industry and Trade Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu
and Colombian Foreign Trade Minister Carlos Ronderos Tarres signed
the agreement, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Tariceanu said Colombia is
interested in using Romania's oil processing equipment and it
intended to use Romania as a transfer center to export bananas to
Central and Eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, Romania's export to
Colombia stood at 5.1 million U.S. dollars, while its import from
the Latin American country was 5.53 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Romania had a trade surplus with Colombia with 16.25
million dollars of export and 5.1 million dollars of import.
</P>
<P>
Romania mainly exports iron and steel products, chemical
products, fertilizer, machine tools, electrical machinery, cars
and jeeps to Colombia while importing coke, automobile parts,
bananas and coffee from the country. 
