<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> True Appraisals of Intangibles Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The State Administration of State
Property (SASP) recently called for putting an end to inflating
appraisals of intangible assets, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Rampant irregular appraisal of intangible assets could
jeopardize China's fledgling valuation business, warned Ni
Jixiang, vice-director-general of SASP's assets valuation center.
</P>
<P>
Intangible assets refer to non-material properties such as
patents, trade marks, copyrights, land-use rights, technologies
and business reputations.
</P>
<P>
Appraisals on intangible assets should be conducted only when
property rights need to be transferred according to set rules
and regulations concerning appraisals, said Ni.
</P>
<P>
However, some valuation agencies violated the rules by offering
business to some enterprises which only intend to advance their
images by using intangible assets vaulation, Ni noted.
</P>
<P>
The malpractice could lure more firms to pay excessive
attention to their intangible assets, thus distracting them from
concentrating on operating their tangible assets.
</P>
<P>
China Appraisal Society is drafting new national standards for
intangible assets appraisal which will be more scientific and
detailed than the existing rules, according to Ni, who is also
deputy secretary-general of the society.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970802.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lenny Sets New U.S. Record in 200-meter Backstroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Lenny Krayzelburg broke the
American record by winning the men's 200-meter backstroke in the
U.S. Swimming National Championships in Nashville, Tennessee on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Krayzelburg claimed gold in 1 minute, 58.04 seconds, 0.29
seconds faster than Tripp Schwenk's record of 1:58.33 set in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Schwenk and Brad Bridgewater, the 1996 Olympic gold medalist in
the event, finished second at 1:59.40 while Schwenk was fifth at
2:02.61.
</P>
<P>
Krayzelburg, who also won the title in the 100m backstroke, is
a native of Russia who became an American citizen in 1995. He
trains with Bridgewater in Los Angeles and won the NCAA 200m
backstroke for Southern California.
</P>
<P>
Van Dyken, the winner of four Olympic gold medals at 1996
Atlanta, proved she is still the favourite. She took the title of
the 50-meter freestyle in 25.10.
</P>
<P>
Misty Hyman took her second national title with a victory in
the 200m butterfly in 2:09.08. Hyman also won the 100m butterfly.
</P>
<P>
Chad Carvin also collected his second gold of the meet with a
victory in the 1,500 freestyle in 15:15.63. Earlier in the
championships, he won the 400-meter freestyle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
