<HEADLINE> Colombia's Producers Price Index Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The producers price
index (PPI) of Colombia fell 0.4 percent in July, the first drop
in the past 12 months, the Bank of the Republic said.
</P>
<P>
A report of the central bank said the domestic items whose
prices dropped included coffee, livestock, legumes and local
produce.
</P>
<P>
The prices of exports dropped 4.4 percent. Coffee's price
decreased 7.1 percent, crude oil 7.2 percent, and flowers 10.3
percent.
</P>
<P>
Producers would get less money for their goods because of this
price reduction.
</P>
<P>
It also means that inflation has been contained and the 18
percent target projected for this year will be achieved, the
report added.
</P>
<P>
The PPI increased 11.7 percent from January to July this year
and 15.5 percent for the last 12 months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
