<HEADLINE> Poland Improves Bank Inspecting System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Polish parliament today adopted a
national banking law designed to improve the inspecting system of
bank operations.
</P>
<P>
According to the law, a committee will be set up to supervise
the work.
</P>
<P>
The chairman of the committee will be appointed by the prime
minister and its members include the national bank president, the
minister or vice-minister of the Finance Ministry, and a
representative of the Polish president.
</P>
<P>
The law also defines the limits of functions and power for the
nine-member Monetary Policy Committee, that is authorized to
determine the national bank's interest rate and compulsory reserve
level. 
</P>
