<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Growth For Hong Kong Investment In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong businessmen established
108 firms in Beijing in the first half of the year, with a total
investment of 519 million US dollars, indicating that Hong Kong
investors are "confident" about their investment in the capital,
officials here say.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has been Beijing's biggest business partner since the
reforms and opening up policy started. Hong Kong investors had set
up 5,228 enterprises by the end of June, accounting for 40 percent
of the city's foreign-financed firms, and Hong Kong investment
came to more than 10.4 billion dollars, accounting for 51 percent
of the city's total investment from outside the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong investors have given priority to urban infrastructure
and hi-tech industries this year, officials say. Hong Kong
businesses in the city have concentrated on real estate and
processing and service industries.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has certain advantages that attract investment,
according to Municipal Economic and Foreign Trade Commission
officials, and the growth of Hong Kong investment makes the city
even more attractive.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's mayor, Jia Qinglin, said recently that the city will
develop policies that encourage overseas business people to invest
in the city's infrastructure and hi-tech industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
