<P>
The province's public security departments investigated and
prosecuted 2,312 criminal cases, down 27.9 percent on the 1996
period. Public security departments handled 1,667 felony cases,
down 30.5 percent the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
The number of major crimes handled during the traditional
Chinese Lunar New Year festival fell by 14.7 percent on last
year's January-March period.
</P>
<P>
Hainan residents note that the island province is safer than
ever before. Public order has improved in rural areas, and 14
of the province's 19 cities and counties reported falling crime
rates.
</P>
<P>
Qiongshan City recorded a 43.3 percent drop and Haikou, the
provincial capital, recorded 30.3 percent decline.
</P>
<P>
Various localities established safe areas and neighborhoods,
Public security departments conducted a legal awareness drive and
carried out an extensive campaign against organized
crimes. Related departments arrested 7,339 members of 1,859
criminal groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
