<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Achieves Better Economic Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region has reported a good agricultural harvest and fast
development in animal husbandry as well as an industrial output
which is higher than the national average during the first half of
the year.
</P>
<P>
The regional statistics bureau show that despite heavy snow,
drought and damage from pests, the region has set new records in
grain, cotton and meat production during the January-June
period. The grain production stood at 4.47 million tons,
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the region had an added value of 13.4 billion yuan
in industrial output, higher than the average level for a province
or autonomous region. Its production-marketing rate was 95
percent, also higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
The region's investment in fixed assets registered a rise of 11
percent during the six months to 10.9 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, Xinjiang's foreign trade volume rose
33 percent to 650 million US dollars during the period. 
