<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai, Taiwan Expand Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The exchanges between Shanghai
and Taiwan witnessed steady growth during the first half of the
year, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
During the period, 225 people from Shanghai were invited to
Taiwan to carry out 53 cooperative activities in cultural,
educational, scientific and technological, as well as aviation and
postal fields. Taiwanese people in return have been invited to
hold a total of 87 cooperative events in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Education experts and teachers are working together to bring
contacts between Shanghai and Taiwan to a higher level, and
more young people have participated in the joint activities.
</P>
<P>
Short-term research in social sciences, medical science and
other scientific areas also is increasing.
</P>
<P>
Contact among professionals in areas of sea transportation,
aviation, posts and telecommunications has also taken a major step
forward; more symposiums have been held and delegations have
swapped visits.
</P>
<P>
The friendly relationship between the Shanghai Federation of
Trade Unions and the central and south parts of Taiwan has great
influence on industrial circles of the island.
</P>
<P>
Artists from both sides are interested in working together on
projects such as lecture tours and professional training
courses. The Shanghai Huai Opera Troupe and Shanghai Puppet Show
Troupe and some other small art groups have performed in Taiwan.
</P>
</TEXT>
