-- The Tokyo Stock Exchange suffered its worst-ever technical
failure when a programming bug in the computerized trading system
shut down the entire system throughout Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
-- Major Japanese computer makers such as Futitsu and Toshiba
are actively opening up Chinese market by establishing
subsidiaries in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
