<HEADLINE> Hingis Enters Semi-finals at Toshiba Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 1 (Xinhua) -- World number one and
top-seeded Martina Hingis entered the semi-finals of the Toshiba
Open women's tennis tournament after beating Conchita Martinez of
Spain at Carlsbad, California, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis played a very tight match against the seventh-seeded
Martinez and eventually won the match 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Hingis enjoyed a big second-set lead but she let seven match
points slip away before finally edging Martinez.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will play against the winner of the match between Mary
Pierce and SAndrine Testud in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The victory over Martinez promoted Hingis' record to 52-1 this
y 16-year-old Swiss girl attempts to win her ninth title in 10
tournaments this season.
</P>
<P>
Hingis has won the Australian Open and Wimbledon Open this
year. The major title that eluded her was the French Open where
she lost her only match of the year in the finals to Iva Majoli.
</P>
</TEXT>
