<HEADLINE> Senior Citizen of Shanghai Donates Writing Samples of Notables </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai resident Zhao Qingge,
83, has donated over 200 rare writing samples of famous
Chinese literary figures to the Shanghai Library.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, who graduated from the Shanghai Fine Arts School in the
early 1930s, was a top editor at a number of prestigious
periodicals during the Anti-Japanese War (1937-1945).
</P>
<P>
As an expert on contemporary literature, Zhao has many friends
who played an important role in China's literary history and
gained world-wide renown, such as Guo Moruo, Mao Dun, Ba Jin, Ding
Ling, Lao She, and Liang Shiqiu.
</P>
<P>
Included in Zhao's gift are 168 letters from her famous
friends, and 56 examples of their handwriting or signature on
paintings.
</P>
<P>
The donation will be kept by the Center of Notable's
Manuscripts, which was set up by the Shanghai Library in 1992.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
