<HEADLINE> IAAF President Becomes Honorary Citizen of Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur
Athletics Federation President Primo Nebiolo was named an Honorary
Citizen of Athens by Mayor Dimitri Avramopoulos in a ceremony at
Athens City Hall here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nebiolo said: "I am honoured to receive this award. But I must
emphasised that it has been given to me as a representative of the
international athletics movement. So I would like to thank my
colleagues from the IAAF Council who are here with me and who work
so hard for the sport."
</P>
<P>
After making the award, Avramopoulos joked:" Now you can vote
me." Nebiolo replied: "Tell me the election date and I will come
back. I think you are doing a very good job."
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony of the 6th World Athletics Championships
took place tonight at the Panithonaikon Stadium with a total of
200 nations and regions attending the competition starting
tomorrow at the Olympic Stadium. 
</P>
